transcript.text: Hello, in this video we will learn about how to add a private store.
Let's talk about the key features and benefits.
It allows you to create a custom store for your B to B customers.
You can create products for a specific private store and accordingly can showcase the pricing.
It allows you to enable the quick checkout feature on the homepage.
You can set order approval rules based on various roles.
Let's have a look into admin.
Go to Store management stores.
Click on Add button.
You need to enter store mandatory details like store name, e-mail, directory name, username and password.
Add as a front customer.
This will add a front end customer with the same store details.
Under configuration settings, you can select the default or custom option in payment, shipping language, currency, country, etc.

Where the default will include all the active options available to store users whereas custom will include only selected options from here which will be available to store users content settings you can enable based on store.
If you select all means all the default store content will be present in the store as well.
If you select only store then you have to create store specific content page, links, banners and sidebar.
Under my accounts.
You can select custom to mark the checkbox for details to be shown on front end.
Under settings you can set markup based on discount or markup price.
Markup Master will be custom which will be applied when product specific markup is not set.
Pay on account You can choose to disable store wise or customer wise and accordingly you can set the pay on account limit.
The department button allows you to create a different departments in a store.
Fixed Billing and Shipping address allows you to control whether you want your end customers to change shipping or billing address during checkout.
Order Approval allows you to enable the order approval feature which gives an option to disable, enable or partially enable for the order approval process.
External Approval It allows your store customers to enter the e-mail address of any external approver in a text box.
Allow user to cancel order It will allow your store customers to cancel an order which is pending for approval by clicking on cancel button.
Show price to customers It allows you to display price on front end.
Also if you disable price visible in front store, make sure Pay on account payment method should enable the continue checkout process.
Quick checkout allows store users to add design from homepage into the cart and make express checkout.
Store fields allows you to take your store customers store information which can be used on studio page to update template information.
Allow tax exemption will make tax calculation AS0 for all store users.
Manage e-mail notification.
If you enable store user only, it will allow you to send e-mail notification to store end users only.
If you enabled store admin only then e-mail notifications will only be sent to store admin.
Access role users and e-mail saved in department Notify button will send acknowledgement e-mail notification to the store admin with admin details.
Keep the status button enabled in order to activate the store and save.
In this way you can create a private store.
Thanks for watching this video.
Feel free to connect with us in case of any queries.
